On Wed, 30 Apr 2003, George Lyle wrote:

> On Wed, 30 Apr 2003 sethmatteson(-at-)att.net wrote:
> 
> > Is there any difference in a 69 and a 76 axl? I have the ones off of my 76
> > laying around and my 69 is in need of some new boots. Never done the job before
> > so which manual is recommended to follow. I've got Haynes, Bentley and Muir?
> 
> All bay bus axles interchange except between manual and auto tranmission
> models

NOT!  Bus bay axles come in three lengths, 

manual tranny half shafts are all 476mm long
auto tranny half shafts are  left side  457mm long
                             right side 505mm long


THEY ARE NOT INTERCHANGABLE

all CVs are the same and are interchangeable

